## 📋 Run Legend – Understanding the JSON Files

### run_metadata.json
Machine-readable information about the run:
- Run ID, start/end dates
- Process steps executed
- Team members involved
- Status (draft, in-review, approved, completed)

### run_log.json
Timestamped log of all activities:
- Each step/decision with timestamp
- Who performed action
- What was produced

### approval_decisions.json
Record of all approvals:
- What was approved (artifact, decision)
- Who approved
- When
- Any conditions

### consultation_requests.json
Queries to experts/stakeholders:
- Question
- To whom
- When asked

### consultation_responses.json
Responses to queries:
- Response content
- Expert/stakeholder name
- Notes

### artifact_state.json
Completion status of each artifact:
- Artifact name
- Status (draft, review, approved, final)
- Version

### informed_role_briefs.json
Communication log:
- Who was informed
- What they were told
- When

### expert_context.json
Background info used:
- Expert names & roles
- Their areas of expertise
- Key inputs they provided

